label.value: pathogen morphology phenotype during colonization of host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype which affects the pathogen morphology during host colonization. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: abnormal pathogen morphology during colonization of host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the pathogen during host colonization is abnormal. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: abnormal pathogen swollen terminal hyphae during cell to cell migration

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the pathogen terminal hyphae during host colonization is abnormal. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: abnormal organization of pathogen septin collar during cell to cell migration

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the pathogen septin collar (GO:0032173) during host colonization is abnormal. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.
update Go term when available to 'septin collar of invasive fungi'

label.value: host morphology phenotype during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype which affects the host morphology during pathogen invasion. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism

label.value: normal formation of extra-invasive hyphal membrane

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the host extra-invasive hyphal membrane (GO:0085039) during pathogen invasion is normal (indistinguishable from wild type). This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: normal pathogen morphology during colonization of host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the pathogen during host colonization is normal (indistinguishable from wild type). This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: normal host morphology during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the host during pathogen invasion is normal (indistinguishable from wild type). This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: abnormal host morphology during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the host during pathogen invasion is abnormal. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.
A phenotype in which a specific transport process is abnormal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: abnormal vesicle-mediated transport during vegetative growth

definition.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vesicle-mediated transport is abnormal.

label.value: normal vesicle-mediated transport during vegetative growth

definition.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vesicle-mediated transport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single organism cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased level of host defense-induced callose deposition

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced callose deposition usually present during infection is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased level of host defense-induced callose deposition

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced callose deposition usually present during infection is lower than normal.
A single species phenotype where the slender tubular outgrowth first produced by most spores in germination is longer than normal. (GO:0032179)
A cellular process phenotype in which asexual spore germination is abnormal (GO:0009847).

label.value: decreased rate of asexual spore germination

definition.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the rate, or speed, of asexual spore germination is decreased.
A phenotype in which a population of a single-species shows increased sensitivity to calcofluor white, manifested as an affect on the extent of population growth. (CHEBI:50011)
A phenotype in which a population of a single-species shows increased sensitivity to congo red, manifested as an affect on the extent of population growth. (CHEBI:34653).
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of cyclic AMP measured in a cell differs from normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of cyclic AMP measured in a cell is lower than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of cyclic AMP measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell differs from normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is higher than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis.

label.value: abolished protein localization to plasma membrane

definition.value: A single organism phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane is abolished (GO:0072659).
We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to plasma membrane, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm

definition.value: A single organism phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane is abolished, and the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.
We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of toxin measured in a cell differs from normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of toxin measured in a cell is lower than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of pyocyanin measured in a cell is lower than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of pyocyanin measured in a cell is too low to detect.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: decreased level of substance in cell

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of substance in cell

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of toxin measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: normal level of substance in cell

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of toxin measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: level of pathogen produced toxin within host phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of pathogen produced toxin during host infection.

label.value: decreased level of pathogen produced toxin within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen produced toxin usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of pathogen produced toxin within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen produced toxin usually present during infection is higher than normal.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the pathogen produced toxin usually present during infection is absent or at a level too low to detect.
A single species population phenotype affecting the shape of a colony of unicellular individuals.

Note that colony morphology terms are not used in PHIPO to annotate filamentous-form colonies because these phenotypes can be related to specific growth terms for hyphal colony morphology please search for PHIPO:0001214 (hyphal growth phenotype). For unicellular colony morphology at the usual resolution it is usually not possible to make any statement about an individual. For dimorphic pathogens these terms are suitable for yeast-form colony phenotypes.
A single species phenotype where the shape of a colony of unicellular individuals is abnormal.

For dimorphic pathogens these terms are suitable for yeast-form colony phenotypes.
A single species colony shape phenotype where the colony is smoother than normal.

A single species phenotype where the shape of a colony of unicellular individuals is normal (indistinguishable from wild type).

A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of pyocyanin measured in a cell is higher than normal.
A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell differs from normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.
